  <text xml:lang="ta" type="edition">
    <body>
        <div rend="parallel">
            <lg xml:id="TK16">
<l>vicumpiṟ ṟuḷivīḻi ṉallāṉmaṟ ṟāṅkē</l>
<l>pacumpuṟ ṟalaikāṇ paritu</l>            
            </lg>
            <lg xml:lang="en">
<l>If drops stopped falling from heaven, it would soon</l>
<l>be hard to see a speartip of green grass.</l>
            </lg>
        </div>
    </body>
  </text>
  <text xml:lang="ta" type="edition">
    <body>
      <head>Parimēlaḻakar</head>
      <div rend="parallel">
        <p xml:id="TK16_P1">
          (i-ḷ). mēkattiṟ ṟuḷivīḻiṟ kāṇpatallatu vīṟātāyiṉ appoḻutē pacumpulliṉatu talaiyaiyuṅ kāṇṭalaritu, (e-ṟu).
        </p>
        <p xml:lang="en">
          The meaning ... : Unless the raindrop is seen in its fall(??) from the cloud—[that is?], if it does not fall—at that very time, seeing even the tip of the green grass is scarcely possible.
        </p>
      </div>
      <div rend="parallel">
        <p xml:id="TK16_P2">
          vicumpu — ākupeyar. maṟṟu viṉaimāṟṟiṉkaṇ vantatu. iḻiva ciṟappummai vikārattāṟ ṟokkatu. ōraṟi vuyirum illai yeṉpatām.
        </p>
        <p xml:lang="en">
          "Vicumpu," [whose basic meaning is sky/heaven, is here] a noun used in a transferred sense[—namely, that of "cloud"]. "Maṟṟu" ["then"?] occurs in the sense of alternation of verbs. [In the phrase "the tip of green grass"], a particle -um [= "even"] conveying an extreme of lowliness has been elided [more lit. "contracted"] through [poetic] license. The [meaning of this phrase] is that there would no [longer] be even a single sentient being(?).
        </p>
      </div>
    </body>
  </text>
  <text xml:lang="ta" type="edition">
    <body>
      <head>Maṇakkuṭavar (15)</head>
      <div rend="parallel">
        <p xml:id="TK16_M1">
          (i - ḷ.) vāṉiṉṟu tuḷivīḻiṉallatu avviṭattup pacutta pulliṉatu tōṟṟamuṅ kāṇṭal aritu, (e - ṟu).
        </p>
        <p xml:lang="en">
          The meaning ... : Unless raindrops fall from heaven(/clouds), even the breaking-through (lit. appearance) of the grass that had been green in that place can scarcely be seen.
        </p>
      </div>
      <div rend="parallel">
        <p xml:id="TK16_M2">
          āṅkeṉpataṉai acaiyākkiṉu mamaiyum. ik̲tu ōraṟivuyiruṅ keṭumeṉṟatu.
        </p>
        <p xml:lang="en">
          If one makes [i.e. interprets] the [word] āṅku ("in that place") as [a metrical filler for] a "half-foot" (acai), that also fits. This [poem] has said that every single sentient being(?) perishes [without rain].
        </p>
      </div>
    </body>
  </text>
